      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KATAMA NZ (2) was 2.75 metres away in third at this track over 2130m last start at her first run back from a spell. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run and rates a primary contender in a similar race. METHUSELAH NZ (4) finished fourth last start over 2130m here, beaten 8 metres. Best recent result was a win at this circuit three starts ago over 2130m. This is a nice drop in grade so he is in the right race to find winning form. SNIPPET (5) finished seventh last start at Group Two level in a race won by Loucasso over 2240m at Melton, beaten 55 metres. This much easier and is sure to be right there at the finish. WAVES OF FORTUNE (6) is in the mix following a sixth at his first run back over 2130m at this course. One for the exotics players.",
